1
00:00:03,108 --> 00:00:08,780
WELCOME TO HIKARI CITY!!
1.2 MILES TO TOWN

2
00:00:16,622 --> 00:00:18,165
[Tetsuo] So it's been three years.

3
00:00:18,999 --> 00:00:21,710
Takao, are you sure you want to do this?

4
00:00:22,919 --> 00:00:23,920
Yeah.

5
00:00:25,756 --> 00:00:28,091
You don't need to, you know.

6
00:00:28,175 --> 00:00:30,635
-We can still--
-I'm all right.

7
00:00:32,346 --> 00:00:36,016
At some point...
I'd have to face it, anyway.

8
00:00:57,788 --> 00:00:59,790
[♪ opening theme music playing]

9
00:01:55,512 --> 00:01:57,764
THE FLOWERS OF EVIL

10
00:01:57,848 --> 00:01:59,975
EPISODE 11

11
00:02:01,560 --> 00:02:03,520
[Takao's cousin] Grandpa!

12
00:02:04,938 --> 00:02:07,858
[sobbing loudly]

13
00:02:11,987 --> 00:02:13,363
Your sister...

14
00:02:26,293 --> 00:02:29,045
-[Tetsuo] Big Sis...
-[Takao's cousin continues crying]

15
00:02:29,129 --> 00:02:31,965
-[Shizue] Haruko...
-[Haruko continues crying]

16
00:02:43,018 --> 00:02:45,187
I really appreciate you coming.

17
00:02:45,270 --> 00:02:47,022
We'll see you again tomorrow.

18
00:02:47,522 --> 00:02:49,733
Thank you for taking care of things.

19
00:02:49,816 --> 00:02:51,985
[Haruko] Do you have a place to stay?

20
00:02:52,068 --> 00:02:53,820
[Tetsuo] Yeah. Don't worry about us.

21
00:02:57,699 --> 00:02:58,950
[Takao's cousin] Taka-chan.

22
00:03:04,456 --> 00:03:05,707
You know...

23
00:03:07,959 --> 00:03:10,128
There's one thing I have to say to you.

24
00:03:14,049 --> 00:03:15,634
It's your fault, Taka-chan.

25
00:03:18,136 --> 00:03:19,846
No one said it to your face,

26
00:03:21,097 --> 00:03:24,309
but we were all amazed
you had the nerve to show your face.

27
00:03:24,810 --> 00:03:26,811
[♪ somber music playing]

28
00:03:27,687 --> 00:03:30,440
Do you have any idea
how difficult you made our lives?

29
00:03:35,153 --> 00:03:37,447
I bet you didn't get to see
Grandpa at the end

30
00:03:38,532 --> 00:03:41,326
because he rejected you, Taka-chan.

31
00:03:45,747 --> 00:03:47,290
I'm sorry.

32
00:03:52,254 --> 00:03:53,672
I sincerely apologize!

33
00:03:54,965 --> 00:03:56,508
If you're actually sorry,

34
00:04:00,262 --> 00:04:02,764
spend the rest of your life
making things right.

35
00:04:14,901 --> 00:04:16,903
[Takao] You're born in this town

36
00:04:17,988 --> 00:04:19,739
and you die in this town.

37
00:04:19,823 --> 00:04:21,741
We're sorry for your loss.
STYLE
::cue()

38
00:04:21,825 --> 00:04:23,994
[Takao] That was supposed
to be my life, too.

39
00:04:24,077 --> 00:04:25,203
KASUGA FUNERAL

40
00:04:25,287 --> 00:04:27,038
But I got out of this town

41
00:04:27,998 --> 00:04:29,875
and continued to live on.

42
00:04:29,958 --> 00:04:31,376
GUEST SIGN IN

43
00:04:31,459 --> 00:04:33,169
Then, what is this town?

44
00:04:34,129 --> 00:04:35,547
What does it mean to me?

45
00:04:35,630 --> 00:04:37,340
MIZUKOSHI INC.
NEIGHBORS

46
00:04:37,424 --> 00:04:39,134
After what he did three years ago...

47
00:04:39,217 --> 00:04:40,802
-I'm shocked they showed up.
-Yeah.

48
00:04:42,846 --> 00:04:46,641
-[male mourner] It is him.
-My goodness. They've got some nerve, no?

49
00:04:46,725 --> 00:04:49,227
After causing that much trouble...

50
00:04:51,521 --> 00:04:53,273
[whispering continues indistinctly]

51
00:04:59,696 --> 00:05:01,531
Takao, are you doing all right?

52
00:05:02,866 --> 00:05:03,867
Yeah.

53
00:05:06,494 --> 00:05:07,621
Dad,

54
00:05:08,830 --> 00:05:10,040
Mom,

55
00:05:12,876 --> 00:05:14,294
I'm sorry.

56
00:05:18,423 --> 00:05:19,633
Thank you.

57
00:05:23,595 --> 00:05:24,888
Takao...

58
00:05:30,143 --> 00:05:32,896
We're very sorry for your loss.

59
00:05:38,485 --> 00:05:39,736
It's been a while.

60
00:05:41,154 --> 00:05:42,697
Kinoshita...

61
00:05:48,328 --> 00:05:49,788
[indistinct chatter]

62
00:05:53,959 --> 00:05:55,085
I'm sorry...

63
00:05:56,044 --> 00:05:57,295
about back then.

64
00:05:59,506 --> 00:06:00,882
[Ai] Right after,

65
00:06:01,466 --> 00:06:04,177
Nanako moved away without even telling me.

66
00:06:06,471 --> 00:06:08,098
I don't know her address.

67
00:06:11,768 --> 00:06:14,479
I guess I could've
tracked her down if I tried.

68
00:06:17,399 --> 00:06:18,525
But, I just...

69
00:06:23,530 --> 00:06:25,281
Have you seen her since then?

70
00:06:27,659 --> 00:06:28,660
Yeah.

71
00:06:28,743 --> 00:06:30,996
What, really? When? Where?

72
00:06:32,288 --> 00:06:34,791
Last year, in Omiya.

73
00:06:36,042 --> 00:06:38,503
-[♪ somber music playing]
-She was with her boyfriend.

74
00:06:39,379 --> 00:06:41,673
Apparently, she lives in Utsunomiya now.

75
00:06:42,966 --> 00:06:44,426
Is she doing all right?

76
00:06:45,427 --> 00:06:46,678
Yeah.

77
00:06:48,221 --> 00:06:50,724
She said she's "happy and stuff."

78
00:06:52,142 --> 00:06:53,351
Right.

79
00:06:57,105 --> 00:06:58,440
[inhales]

80
00:07:01,025 --> 00:07:03,027
I see... [whimpers]

81
00:07:07,782 --> 00:07:11,369
Funny... I've just been left behind.

82
00:07:12,662 --> 00:07:14,914
I drove you guys out of town.

83
00:07:17,625 --> 00:07:20,670
And I couldn't stop Nanako
from leaving, either.

84
00:07:22,130 --> 00:07:23,381
Back then...

85
00:07:24,340 --> 00:07:27,010
what should I have done?

86
00:07:27,886 --> 00:07:29,429
I'm the only one

87
00:07:29,512 --> 00:07:32,015
that's been trapped in this town.

88
00:07:32,098 --> 00:07:35,018
Forever and ever... [sobbing]

89
00:07:36,060 --> 00:07:37,270
I don't want that...

90
00:07:47,655 --> 00:07:49,115
What about Nakamura?

91
00:07:52,327 --> 00:07:55,830
What happened between you two after that?

92
00:08:00,168 --> 00:08:01,628
I haven't seen her.

93
00:08:03,546 --> 00:08:06,216
Not since the moment
she pushed me off the stage.

94
00:08:07,425 --> 00:08:11,304
I don't know... where she is now.

95
00:08:13,473 --> 00:08:14,849
Whether she's alive,

96
00:08:17,060 --> 00:08:18,645
or if she's dead.

97
00:08:22,482 --> 00:08:24,400
Don't you want to see her again?

98
00:08:26,444 --> 00:08:28,988
I hope I can see her again, someday.

99
00:08:30,156 --> 00:08:31,366
[♪ music fades]

100
00:08:31,449 --> 00:08:32,492
Do you want to know?

101
00:08:34,202 --> 00:08:36,037
Do you want to know where she is now?

102
00:08:39,082 --> 00:08:40,083
What?
STYLE
::cue()

103
00:08:42,126 --> 00:08:43,753
-[Aya] You're lying.
-[Kotegawa] It's crazy.

104
00:08:43,837 --> 00:08:46,339
[Aya] You have to be lying.
That can't be true.

105
00:08:48,591 --> 00:08:50,635
Oh... Mornin'.

106
00:08:50,718 --> 00:08:51,719
Morning.

107
00:08:52,303 --> 00:08:54,180
How was Gunma?

108
00:08:54,806 --> 00:08:56,099
Got any souvenirs for us?

109
00:08:56,182 --> 00:08:59,602
Who comes back from a funeral
with souvenirs, idiot?

110
00:09:00,395 --> 00:09:04,607
You know, Tokiwa was feeling lonely
with you absent for two days.

111
00:09:04,691 --> 00:09:06,985
She wouldn't shut up about you.

112
00:09:07,068 --> 00:09:09,154
Hey, that wasn't all I talked about!

113
00:09:09,237 --> 00:09:10,530
[both laughing]

114
00:09:21,249 --> 00:09:23,042
Hey, Kasuga?

115
00:09:23,126 --> 00:09:24,169
Yeah?

116
00:09:26,045 --> 00:09:27,130
If you're free today,

117
00:09:27,630 --> 00:09:30,633
why don't you come over to my place?

118
00:09:44,063 --> 00:09:46,065
-Sorry.
-Hmm?

119
00:09:46,149 --> 00:09:48,693
I should've told you my parents were out.

120
00:09:49,527 --> 00:09:51,529
No, don't worry about it.

121
00:09:53,406 --> 00:09:54,824
The thing is...

122
00:09:58,661 --> 00:09:59,746
I've finished...

123
00:10:01,122 --> 00:10:02,415
my novel.

124
00:10:03,082 --> 00:10:04,083
What?

125
00:10:04,167 --> 00:10:05,793
Seriously? When?

126
00:10:06,377 --> 00:10:07,587
Last night.

127
00:10:23,436 --> 00:10:24,812
Please read it.

128
00:10:29,567 --> 00:10:30,568
Tokiwa...

129
00:10:31,903 --> 00:10:33,029
Congratulations.

130
00:10:35,156 --> 00:10:36,157
But...

131
00:10:38,284 --> 00:10:39,911
I can't read it right now.

132
00:10:42,121 --> 00:10:43,206
There's something...

133
00:10:45,083 --> 00:10:46,876
I need to tell you.

134
00:10:56,844 --> 00:10:58,012
You see,

135
00:10:59,889 --> 00:11:01,307
when I was in junior high,

136
00:11:02,934 --> 00:11:05,270
I made a contract with someone.

137
00:11:06,354 --> 00:11:07,981
[♪ instrumental music playing]

138
00:11:17,407 --> 00:11:18,992
[Takao] That town,

139
00:11:19,075 --> 00:11:21,202
the town I was born and raised in,

140
00:11:21,786 --> 00:11:26,082
is a depressing town
surrounded by mountains.

141
00:11:28,584 --> 00:11:30,253
In my second year of junior high,

142
00:11:32,005 --> 00:11:34,966
I stole the gym clothes
of the girl I had a crush on.

143
00:11:38,136 --> 00:11:39,929
I didn't mean to, though.

144
00:11:41,139 --> 00:11:42,348
I just...

145
00:11:42,432 --> 00:11:46,978
found it on the classroom floor,
and I took it home with me.

146
00:11:47,979 --> 00:11:51,983
This classmate named Nakamura saw me...

147
00:11:52,567 --> 00:11:53,693
SAEKI

148
00:11:53,776 --> 00:11:55,153
...and I ended up

149
00:11:55,903 --> 00:11:58,865
making a contract with Nakamura.

150
00:12:00,950 --> 00:12:02,410
One day, the two of us

151
00:12:03,077 --> 00:12:05,246
destroyed our classroom.

152
00:12:05,747 --> 00:12:08,291
We snuck into the school at night,

153
00:12:08,374 --> 00:12:10,460
used the calligraphy ink and paint,

154
00:12:10,543 --> 00:12:12,420
and turned the place upside down,

155
00:12:12,503 --> 00:12:14,422
changing the classroom

156
00:12:14,505 --> 00:12:17,342
into a chaotic mess,
like no one had ever seen before.

157
00:12:18,009 --> 00:12:19,552
Then, during swimming class,

158
00:12:20,678 --> 00:12:22,889
I snuck into the girls' changing room,

159
00:12:23,598 --> 00:12:26,642
and I stole the panties
of every girl in my class.

160
00:12:28,102 --> 00:12:30,313
It's not like I wanted them or anything.

161
00:12:31,689 --> 00:12:32,982
All I wanted was...

162
00:12:33,066 --> 00:12:34,859
I wanted to make Nakamura...

163
00:12:37,236 --> 00:12:38,738
I just wanted

164
00:12:39,572 --> 00:12:41,407
to see Nakamura laugh.

165
00:12:43,117 --> 00:12:44,327
But, after all,

166
00:12:46,204 --> 00:12:49,165
I never succeeded
in making her truly laugh.

167
00:12:51,959 --> 00:12:53,378
In the end,

168
00:12:54,087 --> 00:12:55,588
I decided

169
00:12:56,130 --> 00:12:58,091
to leave this world with her.

170
00:13:00,802 --> 00:13:02,095
But...

171
00:13:06,349 --> 00:13:08,518
even that was beyond my reach.
STYLE
::cue()

172
00:13:18,945 --> 00:13:23,157
That's the reason I moved here.

173
00:13:31,791 --> 00:13:33,126
[♪ music fades]

174
00:13:36,129 --> 00:13:37,213
Sorry.

175
00:13:38,214 --> 00:13:39,715
You need to leave.

176
00:13:45,471 --> 00:13:47,223
I have to think about this alone.

177
00:13:48,933 --> 00:13:50,059
Please.

178
00:13:52,687 --> 00:13:53,813
I can't leave.

179
00:13:53,896 --> 00:13:54,897
Why?

180
00:13:55,439 --> 00:13:57,108
You're done with your story, right?

181
00:14:01,195 --> 00:14:03,531
[angrily] What do you want from me?

182
00:14:03,614 --> 00:14:05,616
I don't want anything from you.

183
00:14:05,700 --> 00:14:07,994
I just felt like I should tell you.

184
00:14:08,077 --> 00:14:09,871
Don't you think you're being selfish?

185
00:14:10,872 --> 00:14:13,249
All I asked was for you to read my novel.

186
00:14:14,083 --> 00:14:16,335
Did you just want to get this
off your chest?

187
00:14:16,419 --> 00:14:19,005
-No, it's not like that.
-What is it, then?

188
00:14:20,131 --> 00:14:21,257
I...

189
00:14:22,592 --> 00:14:24,468
I don't want to run from it anymore.

190
00:14:25,595 --> 00:14:28,472
Honestly, I thought I'd keep it to myself.

191
00:14:28,556 --> 00:14:30,933
That it'd be selfish
to make you deal with this.

192
00:14:32,602 --> 00:14:33,603
But...

193
00:14:34,103 --> 00:14:35,646
[♪ somber music playing]

194
00:14:35,730 --> 00:14:37,648
the past won't go away.

195
00:14:38,983 --> 00:14:40,318
I realized

196
00:14:40,818 --> 00:14:43,362
I still can't let go of Nakamura.

197
00:14:44,572 --> 00:14:46,574
It's not about liking her or not.

198
00:14:47,909 --> 00:14:49,702
I can't tell if I want to hold her

199
00:14:50,369 --> 00:14:52,121
or be killed by her.

200
00:14:54,332 --> 00:14:55,499
I just...

201
00:14:57,001 --> 00:14:59,378
I just want to see Nakamura again.

202
00:15:02,173 --> 00:15:03,966
So that I can find a life with you.

203
00:15:10,014 --> 00:15:13,267
Nakamura's whereabouts are in this note.

204
00:15:14,227 --> 00:15:16,771
I got it the other day
from a classmate in Gunma.

205
00:15:18,940 --> 00:15:21,692
After I see Nakamura one more time,

206
00:15:22,693 --> 00:15:24,695
if you'd still forgive me...

207
00:15:26,822 --> 00:15:28,199
then...

208
00:15:28,950 --> 00:15:31,077
I'd like to read your novel.

209
00:15:36,457 --> 00:15:38,000
The answer is no.

210
00:15:40,628 --> 00:15:42,213
I can't let you read this.

211
00:15:45,383 --> 00:15:48,302
This seems so silly now, all of a sudden.

212
00:16:02,900 --> 00:16:04,110
Tokiwa!

213
00:16:05,361 --> 00:16:07,780
-[sobbing, panting]
-Wait!

214
00:16:08,656 --> 00:16:09,699
Stop it!

215
00:16:14,245 --> 00:16:15,871
[Takao grunting] Wait!

216
00:16:17,707 --> 00:16:19,250
[Aya] Let go of me!

217
00:16:19,917 --> 00:16:21,252
I said, let go!

218
00:16:21,335 --> 00:16:23,754
[Takao] I won't let go of you, ever!

219
00:16:24,755 --> 00:16:25,923
[Aya grunts]

220
00:16:27,216 --> 00:16:28,759
[panting]

221
00:16:35,850 --> 00:16:36,851
Then...

222
00:16:37,393 --> 00:16:38,894
can you kiss me?

223
00:16:53,034 --> 00:16:55,286
[♪ gentle music playing]

224
00:17:27,485 --> 00:17:28,778
I'll go with you.

225
00:17:29,862 --> 00:17:30,946
What?

226
00:17:32,198 --> 00:17:34,367
I'll go with you to see Nakamura.

227
00:17:43,834 --> 00:17:45,002
[♪ music fades]
STYLE
::cue()

228
00:18:04,230 --> 00:18:10,361
NAKAMURA IS WITH HER MOTHER NOW,
HELPING OUT AT HER DINER IN TOKAWA, CHIBA.

229
00:18:21,622 --> 00:18:28,587
TOKAWA STATION

230
00:18:32,133 --> 00:18:33,426
[sighs]

231
00:18:37,012 --> 00:18:38,139
Let's go.

232
00:18:38,931 --> 00:18:39,932
Okay.

233
00:18:43,894 --> 00:18:46,772
[♪ melancholy music playing]

234
00:18:59,702 --> 00:19:00,911
GUEST HOUSE CHONAN-SO

235
00:19:00,995 --> 00:19:02,163
[Aya] Excuse me.

236
00:19:02,705 --> 00:19:03,789
Yes?

237
00:19:03,873 --> 00:19:07,460
Is there a diner around here?

238
00:19:07,960 --> 00:19:10,629
Sure, there are a few.

239
00:19:10,713 --> 00:19:12,840
One that's run by a mother and daughter?

240
00:19:12,923 --> 00:19:17,595
Ah. You must be looking
for the Mizukoshi's, then.

241
00:19:18,220 --> 00:19:19,263
Mizukoshi Diner.

242
00:19:21,265 --> 00:19:22,808
It's at the end of this road,

243
00:19:23,434 --> 00:19:25,060
but they close at 3:00 p.m.

244
00:19:25,644 --> 00:19:27,146
[Aya] I see.

245
00:19:27,229 --> 00:19:28,689
Thank you very much.

246
00:19:35,571 --> 00:19:36,906
Ah.

247
00:19:38,115 --> 00:19:41,118
MIZUKOSHI DINER

248
00:19:47,708 --> 00:19:50,669
[♪ music fades]

249
00:19:50,753 --> 00:19:53,923
OPENING HOURS 11:00 A.M. - 3:00 P.M.
4:30 P.M. - 8:00 P.M.

250
00:20:01,931 --> 00:20:04,099
Hey, you've got customers.

251
00:20:04,183 --> 00:20:05,184
[owner] Coming!

252
00:20:06,435 --> 00:20:07,895
Hello there, welcome.

253
00:20:08,395 --> 00:20:09,396
A table for two?

254
00:20:10,773 --> 00:20:12,817
-Yes, please.
-[Shino] Right over here.

255
00:20:12,900 --> 00:20:14,985
-[customer] Thanks for lunch!
-[Shino] Thank you.

256
00:20:15,069 --> 00:20:18,072
You must be busy
without your girl helping out.

257
00:20:18,155 --> 00:20:20,616
-[chuckles] Come again soon.
-Will do.

258
00:20:26,288 --> 00:20:27,498
Hmm?

259
00:20:27,581 --> 00:20:29,416
[chuckles] Please sit.

260
00:20:36,590 --> 00:20:38,759
Is that... her mom?

261
00:20:44,348 --> 00:20:46,892
Have you decided on your order?

262
00:20:48,310 --> 00:20:50,229
I'll have the fried mackerel set meal.

263
00:20:50,312 --> 00:20:51,313
All right.

264
00:20:51,397 --> 00:20:52,398
And you?

265
00:20:52,481 --> 00:20:55,067
I'll have... the same thing.
STYLE
::cue()

266
00:20:55,150 --> 00:20:57,444
Sure. I'll have those out in a bit.

267
00:21:09,415 --> 00:21:11,375
[door slides open dramatically]

268
00:21:28,183 --> 00:21:29,935
[♪ dramatic music playing]

269
00:21:41,113 --> 00:21:42,698
[Takao] It smells like...

270
00:21:44,074 --> 00:21:45,200
[Sawa] I'm back.

271
00:21:45,284 --> 00:21:46,410
[Shino] Welcome back.

272
00:21:49,538 --> 00:21:51,540
[Sawa] They only had
small bottles of soy sauce.

273
00:21:51,624 --> 00:21:53,459
[Shino] I see. Thanks for getting these.

274
00:21:54,293 --> 00:21:56,962
-Take this to that table, would you?
-[Sawa] Sure.

275
00:22:02,509 --> 00:22:05,804
Here's the fried mackerel set meal.

276
00:22:07,514 --> 00:22:09,600
I'll be back with another.

277
00:22:13,020 --> 00:22:14,188
Hey!

278
00:22:14,271 --> 00:22:15,439
[♪ music fades]

279
00:22:15,522 --> 00:22:16,982
Nakamura...

280
00:22:18,442 --> 00:22:20,235
Do you remember me?

281
00:22:22,071 --> 00:22:23,322
It's me, Kasuga.

282
00:22:24,156 --> 00:22:25,616
Takao Kasuga.

283
00:22:27,534 --> 00:22:28,994
I came to see you.

284
00:22:29,078 --> 00:22:31,080
[♪ gripping music playing]

285
00:22:48,722 --> 00:22:50,891
TO BE CONTINUED

286
00:22:50,975 --> 00:22:52,977
[♪ closing theme music playing]

287
00:23:48,032 --> 00:23:49,033
ON THE NEXT EPISODE

288
00:23:49,116 --> 00:23:52,870
[narrator] Kasuga and Nakamura
are reunited.

289
00:23:52,953 --> 00:23:56,665
Tokiwa quietly watches over them.

290
00:23:56,749 --> 00:24:01,879
Next, on the final episode,
see the other side of The Flowers of Evil.

291
00:24:01,962 --> 00:24:02,963
Translated by Yuka Kristi

